   location if the two ever conflict.
   "Licensor" means StarFang.
   "Individual" means a single natural person who uses the Software alone, doing
   the hands-on work themselves and not sharing use of the Software with any other
   person. A single natural person is an Individual even when the work is paid and
   even when the output is delivered to or used by an Organization client, and even
   when that person operates through their own one-person legal vehicle. The
   deliverables an Individual produces with the Software are not themselves the
   Software; a client who only receives those deliverables is not, for that reason,
   an Organization user. This Individual definition prevails over the general
   "by, or for an Organization" language wherever they would otherwise conflict.
   "Organization" means any entity that is not a single natural person, including
   any company, partnership, non-profit, educational institution, government body,
   or association, and any group of two or more people working together. Use of the
   Software is Organization use when two or more natural persons use, run, or
   operate the Software, or when an Organization runs the Software itself.
   "Developer" means each natural person who uses, runs, or operates the Software in
   or for an Organization, whether or not that person writes code. A Commercial Seat
   License is required for each Developer.
   "Commercial Seat License" means a separate paid license from the Licensor, one
   seat per Developer, set out in a signed commercial agreement.

